十一、計畫表公佈後異動說明 Changes Made After Posting Syllabus

The main objective of this course is to provide an introduction to the works of some of the most influential 20th-21st Century political philosophers. The course is organized around  three  thematic  areas:  (1)  What  is  Political  Philosophy?  (2)  Definitions  of  the Political  (3)  Radical  Voices.  We  will  analyze  the  concepts  articulated  by  these philosophers,  paying  attention  to  their  divergent  perspectives  on  some  of  the  most important questions of contemporary political philosophy.









